---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { contactEmail, siteConfig } from "../../data/site";
import "../../styles/content-pages.css";
---

<Layout
	title="Privacy policy | mozgrozmowy.pl"
	description="Privacy and data processing information for mozgrozmowy.pl."
	lang="en"
	pathname="/en/privacy-policy/"
	alternatePath="/privacy-policy/"
>
	<main class="page-shell">
		<section class="page-intro page-intro--alt">
			<p class="page-kicker">Privacy</p>
			<h1>Privacy policy</h1>
			<p>
				This website is intentionally simple: it publishes content and does not use
				tracking tools for user profiling.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="about-card surface-card">
			<h2>1. Website controller</h2>
			<p>
				The controller of personal data processed in connection with the operation
				of mozgrozmowy.pl is {siteConfig.author.name}. For privacy-related matters,
				you can contact me by email at
				<a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
			</p>

			<h2>2. What data may be processed</h2>
			<p>
				The website does not use user accounts, registration forms, marketing
				forms, or tools designed to track users across pages or services.
			</p>
			<p>
				From a technical perspective, the server and hosting provider may process
				basic data necessary to display the website and maintain security, such as
				IP address, request date, browser type, or server logs.
			</p>

			<h2>3. Cookies</h2>
			<p>
				At the time of publication, the website does not use non-essential cookies
				for analytics, advertising, or marketing purposes.
			</p>
			<p>
				If such features are added in the future, this privacy policy will be
				updated accordingly.
			</p>

			<h2>4. Email contact and legal bases</h2>
			<p>
				If you contact me by email, I process the data included in your message
				only for the purpose of replying and continuing communication about that
				matter.
			</p>
			<p>
				The legal basis for processing is Article 6(1)(f) GDPR, i.e. my legitimate
				interest in handling correspondence and responding to messages. If your
				message concerns entering into or performing a contract, or taking steps at
				your request prior to entering into a contract, the legal basis may also be
				Article 6(1)(b) GDPR.
			</p>

			<h2>5. Data recipients and retention period</h2>
			<p>
				Data recipients may include entities providing technical maintenance for the
				website, in particular the hosting provider and email service provider,
				only to the extent necessary for the provision of those services.
			</p>
			<p>
				Data related to email correspondence is stored for the time necessary to
				handle the contact, and afterwards for the period needed to defend against
				possible claims or document the course of correspondence where justified.
				Technical data and server logs are stored for the time necessary to ensure
				security and the proper operation of the website.
			</p>

			<h2>6. Your rights</h2>
			<p>
				You have the right to information about data processing, access to your
				data, rectification, erasure, restriction of processing, and — where
				provided by law — to object to processing.
			</p>
			<p>
				You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the President of the
				Personal Data Protection Office in Poland if you believe that the
				processing of your data violates the GDPR.
			</p>

			<h2>7. Changes</h2>
			<p>
				This policy may be updated in the future if the technical operation of the
				website or the scope of data processing changes.
			</p>
			<p>
				Last updated: April 25, 2026.
			</p>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
